            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> why 0.12 milestone?\n\nMostly because it affects the functionality that is added in 0.12. Namely `an` and `in` default mappings.\n\nAs it is now, there is no (good) way to use custom mappings for those. While when they were only LSP based - there was.\n\nSo deciding now and not after the release (as the tree-sitter functionality was already merged this late in the development cycle) seems like a good idea.",
