            "body": "> > why 0.12 milestone?\n> \n> Mostly because it affects the functionality that is added in 0.12. Namely `an` and `in` default mappings.\n\nmappings are easy to change later, but public APIs are not. \nwe can always include this in 0.12.1 or some other followup release.\n\n> Another approach can be a `vim.treesitter.select(opts)` function with `opts = { direction = 'parent'|'child'|'next'|'prev', count = integer }`\n\nThat aligns with `lsp.buf.selection_range({direction}`. Not sure that \"selection\" is a topic that deserves its own module.\n\n@Desel72 if you are going to use AI you must (1) clean it up and (2) at least make the formatting readable. This is the only warning I will give.",
