            "body": "> mappings are easy to change later, but public APIs are not.\n\nIt exactly about the fact that without public method it is *not* easy for users to change the mapping for this action.\n\n> > Another approach can be a `vim.treesitter.select(opts)` function with `opts = { direction = 'parent'|'child'|'next'|'prev', count = integer }`\n> \n> That aligns with `lsp.buf.selection_range({direction}`. Not sure that \"selection\" is a topic that deserves its own module.\n\nMy only concern was that `vim.lsp.buf.selection_range()` uses a somewhat esoteric integer `direction`. Which might be suitable for it specifically, but not really adaptable in case of tree-sitter. Since direction is not only \"one dimensional\".",
